I chose my first medium because I think that graphite is really pretty on paper and it is easy to use a variety of values. The image quality changed a lot when I went to printmaking. The quality got worse than before, and it looks like it is more AI generated and the graphite generation. The graphite medium communicates more realism, and it flows well. Also looking like an actual drawing on the other hand the linocut print communicates more of just a basic artwork. I noticed a big difference in the boldness in the print making generation as well. The lines are bolder, which I think conveys a message better. Tools and processes shaped the outcome of these generations because my use of certain words, such as texture or shading, made the artwork come out a specific way. If I didn't use those tools, the AI would have had to make the generation out of a broader explanation. The printmaking did change my interpretation of the peace because it was so different from the graphite, drawing that it made me see something new. The graphite was very real looking and uses the medium well to add value in texture. The linocut print did a great job at adding board lines, but I don't see as much texture and I see less of a story.
